DIGEST
SB 502 Original 2026 Regular Session Cathey
Present law prohibits parish governing authorities from adopting ordinances that declares
an agricultural operation operated in accordance with generally accepted agricultural
practices or traditional farm practices to be a nuisance or zoning ordinance that forces
closure of the agricultural operation.
Proposed law retains present law and further prohibits a parish or municipal governing
authority from enacting or enforcing any ordinance prohibiting the storage of sugarcane
bagasse biomass when stored in accordance with a best management practice plan.
Proposed law defines "sugarcane bagasse biomass".
